  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2017-07-28",
    "date": "2019-09-06T15:30:13Z",
    "text": "Addiction Recovery for Rural Communities Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Agriculture (USDA) to provide financial assistance for the construction of facilities and systems in rural areas for substance-use disorder services.\n\nIn selecting recipients of loans and grants to establish community facilities, USDA must give priority to developers of facilities that: (1) provide substance use disorder prevention, treatment, or recovery services; and (2) employ staff with expertise and training in identifying and treating individuals with substance-use disorders. \n\nIn providing grants to establish individual and family health education programs, USDA must give priority to entities\u00a0intending to\u00a0use the funds for substance-use disorder education, treatment, and prevention."
  },
